{
  "stem": "3631.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I stood, next to me, and [INAUDIBLE], was a fellow by the name of Raab, R-A-A-B, who-- a nice fellow.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was an office worker, too.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he stepped out of line, and the sergeant came up and shot him, just-- just for that.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember the name of the sergeant was [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Stoyevsky. ?] [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I passed out at this point, and they took me to the sick-- sick bay, which in itself was dangerous.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I got through it and it was all right.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we had to be counted three times-- two or three times a day, where we stood there by barracks and the-- each barrack has a-- had a barrack elder, like one Jew in charge of the barrack who was responsible for-- for the barrack.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Like each work group had a capo, a head man, and he was responsible.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] the ghetto-- [PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] the ghetto was liquidated on March 13th, '43, so that must be the day, or a few days before-- before we got into the-- into the camp.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A hundred people remained to-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] to clean up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on this day, hundreds of children and grown ups stayed in the ghetto, as they were not permitted to go in the work-- walk to the camp-- and shot.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's that was March-- around March 13, '43, I think.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Plaszow?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well again, I stood around for awhile, and again, I found a job in-- in the office.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a type-- they call in German, called it Schreiber.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Maybe you call it a scribe.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Screeb?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A scribe?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What do you think?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Taking correspondence and office-- office jobs.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
